Text: In this section, you will be presented with a series of objects. Please name as many possible uses for this object as you can think of by typing them in the box below each object.

Please keep in mind that a single object will have more than one use. For example, a ball can be thrown or can be bounced or even stepped on. When listing multiple uses for one object, please separate each use with a comma (i.e., thrown, bounced, stepped on)
Before starting the experiment, you will complete a short practice sesstion. Press ENTER when you are ready to begin.
You have completed this section. Press ENTER to continue
You will now start the full experiment. Press ENTER when you are ready to begin.
You will now be asked a few questions about your experience today.
